# Terminal Command Execution

This project uses PowerShell as the default shell. Standard Unix command separators like `&&` are not valid in this environment and will cause parser errors.

## Rule: Use `;` instead of `&&`

When executing multiple terminal commands in a single shell call, ALWAYS use the semicolon `;` as the command separator.

### Examples

#### ❌ BAD (Unix-style)
```bash
git status && git diff && git log -5
```

#### ✅ GOOD (PowerShell-compatible)
```powershell
git status; git diff; git log -5
```

## Note on Command Independence
Using `;` ensures that subsequent commands execute even if earlier ones fail. This is generally preferred in this environment to avoid `ParserError: The token '&&' is not a valid statement separator`.
